<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-01-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-01-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="345" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d345">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">150.071 Control/194</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Swedish Minister</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Boström</hi>)</head>
                        <p>In view of the fact that a new Bill (S. 379), to provide for the
                            deportation of certain alien seamen and for other purposes, has now been
                            introduced by Senator King,<note n="2" xml:id="d345fn2">Introduced on
                                January 7, 1935, by Senator William H. King of Utah; <hi rend="italic">Congressional Record</hi>, vol. 79, pt. 1, p.
                                136.</note> the Minister of Sweden begs respectfully to call
                            attention to his memorandum of March 9, 1934,<note n="3" xml:id="d345fn3">
                                <ref target="frus1934v01#pg_756">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1934, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 756</ref>.</note> left at the
                            Department of State on the same date.</p>
                        <p>The Minister would highly appreciate it if the facts therein set forth
                            could be given due consideration.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <dateline rendition="#left">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-01-22">January
                                    22, 1935</date>.</dateline>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>